name: Pizza
description: The crust, based on a recipe whose supposed provenance is Italy, has an unusual flaky/tender texture, and great taste — courtesy of three types of fat: vegetable oil, olive oil, and butter. Also, the tiny bit of cornmeal adds subtle but delightful crunch.

name: Tuscan White Bean Pasta
description: This Tuscan White Bean Pasta is definitely our type of recipe: uses a lot of fresh ingredients, is very filling, and flavorful. This pasta packs protein (white beans and parmesan), veggies (tomatoes and spinach), and carbohydrates (pasta), making it a great one-dish meal. You can serve it up as is for a lighter main dish, or add some sliced grilled chicken to make it a bit more filling.

name: Lasagna
description: Everyone loves a good lasagna, right? It’s a great way to feed a crowd and a perfect dish to bring to a potluck. It freezes well. It reheats well. Leftovers will keep you happy for days.

name: Sushi
description: Feel free to eat your sushi rolls or nigiri with your hands! This is, in fact, how many in Japan eat their sushi. When eating nigiri, it's also recommended to turn the roll upside-down to dip in soy sauce to avoid absorbing too much into the rice

name: Steak and fries
description: These Loaded Steak Fries are topped with gooey cheese and perfectly grilled steak to make the perfect party appetizer recipe!

name: Hamburger
description: Hand crafted with 100% Angus beef. We use fresh, natural and delicious ingredients. Made to order and served medium, on toasty, classic style buns.

name: Hot dog
description: From Seattle's hot dog topped with cream cheese, onions, and mustard, to Jersey's bacon-wrapped ripper take a trip around the country via the  express without ever leaving your kitchen! Each recipe pays authentic tribute to the city's original version, giving you the chance to really get a taste of a local favorite. Try all eight for the ultimate journey

name: Fried Chicken
description: This classic recipe is Southern fried chicken at its easiest. Crispy and juicy, it's sure to be a family favorite. Serve alongside mashed potatoes, coleslaw, creamed corn, or another vegetable side dish. This dish calls for bone-in pieces—however, other recipes use boneless chicken breasts or boneless chicken thighs with equally delicious results. If you're looking for a little more spice, this KFC-style chicken delivers.

name: Salmon
description: This Garlic Butter Baked Salmon recipe makes tender, flaky salmon brushed with an incredible garlic butter sauce! Baked on a sheet pan with your favorite veggies, this easy salmon recipe takes just a few minutes of prep and makes a perfect weeknight dinner idea.

name: Chicken Curry
description: Chicken curry stewed in coconut milk and curry spices is a hearty and tasty dish the whole family will love. Easy to make and cooks in one pan!

name: Shrimp
description: This honey garlic shrimp is one of the most popular recipes on this website because it’s not only lip-smacking delicious, it’s a very quick and easy dinner recipe. Ready in 20 minutes, this healthy dinner will join your regular dinner rotation. Serve with brown rice and vegetables, grill on skewers, or serve over salad.

name: Salad
description: This salad is perfect for summer cookouts and easy family dinners, and are some of the best ways to use the season's delicious fruits and veggies

name: Tuna
description: Looking for a tasty protein fix after a workout, or a lunch that will fill you up? Try a tuna and egg Niçoise pot, delivering 30g of protein per portion

name: Soup
description: A delicious, spicy blend, packed full of iron and low fat to boot.

name: Ribs
description: These Easy Oven Baked Ribs are one of the tastiest recipes ever. Cooked low and slow, which makes them so flavorful and fall off the bone tender.

name: Carbonara
description: This Creamy Carbonara recipe is a plate of heavenly, creamy pasta. Silky spaghetti with crispy pancetta in a super creamy and cheesy sauce. Simply delicious and so easy to make at home

name: Grilled Octopus
description: Easy Grilled Octopus Recipe – tender, lightly seasoned and charred octopus that tastes amazing!

name: Strayberry Ice-cream
description: This homemade Strawberry Ice Cream recipe is an easy summer dessert full of fresh strawberry flavor. This easy strawberry ice cream is creamy and dreamy.
